      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument against nuclear is a classic case of technological optimism over established engineering realities. While battery storage and smart grids are advancing rapidly, they currently lack the massive, long-duration storage capacity required to reliably power an entire industrialized grid through weeks of low renewable output. Nuclear provides immediate, proven, high-density power that batteries cannot yet match at scale, making it a necessary partner in the energy transition.",
      "source": "target",
